About Livonia Michigan

Sitting in the northwest part of Wayne County just north of downtown Detroit is the city of Livonia, Michigan. The majority of Livonia is a collection of neighborhoods acting as a suburb of the Metro Detroit area, with freeways connecting the neighborhood areas to the city itself. Originally settled by New York and New England settlers, the Livonia Township was established in 1835 and named after existing settlement of the same name in New York and Pennsylvania. Livonia Township became the city of Livonia when it was officially incorporated in 1950. Livonia has hosted several U.S. Presidents, including Richard Nixon, Gerald Ford, Ronald Reagan, George H.W. Bush, Bill Clinton, and George W. Bush.
